<title type="html"><![CDATA[8/28 (Sat.) Peyo the horse visits sick people/ Happiest &amp; healthiest people on this planet, curious case...(Mei)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=536&amp;p=559#p559"><![CDATA[
8/28 (Sat.) Peyo the horse visits sick people/<br />Happiest &amp; healthiest people on this planet, curious case of Hunza tribe! (Host: Mei)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited, 2 mins/each member)<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2 discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation<br /><br />Place: Zoom meeting<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... 09#success<br /><br />會議 ID: 929 8726 6213<br />密碼: 112233<br /><br />Session 1. Peyo the horse visits sick people<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://youtu.be/XypgQoOBuBk">https://youtu.be/XypgQoOBuBk</a><!-- m --><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://youtu.be/HrDsVAlGI_s">https://youtu.be/HrDsVAlGI_s</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1. Do you think some animals have a unique sense of spirituality with human beings like Peyo. Please share your experiences or the story heard.<br /><br />2. What do you think about pet therapy? do you think it really gives benefits to patients?<br /><br />3. If you are a director of a hospital in Taiwan, would you allow a trained horse to join the therapy team as a company for patients interested? And why?<br /><br />4. Have you or your relative/ friend had the experience of staying in a hospital for treatment? How did they overcome their fear or uncertainty?<br /><br />------------------------------------------------------------<br />Session 2. Happiest &amp; healthiest people on this planet, curious case of Hunza tribe!<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zeenews.india.com/photos/world/happiest-healthiest-people-on-this-planet-curious-case-of-hunza-tribe-2357101">https://zeenews.india.com/photos/world/ ... be-2357101</a><!-- m --><br />Hunza Valley View~ <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F8cYhngAZfI&amp;t=665s">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F8cYhngAZfI&amp;t=665s</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1. Please use your own words to describe why most Hunza tribe people can live up to 100 years old?<br /><br />2. What do you think that except for Hunza tribe people why in other tribes or developed countries people can't live as long as the Hunza tribe people?<br /><br />3. If you have to choose between 1. being a rich person, 2. living a long and happy life in Hunza village, and 3. being an ordinary free person, which one would you choose and why? <br /><br />4. Conversation practice:<br />In your subgroup, each person please think of a question related to this article then ask your fellow group members.<br /><br />P.S.<br />1.因疫情關係，聚會方式改為線上遠距。<br />2.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12531">Danny Lin</a> — Tue Aug 24, 2021 7:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
